Write a Java program to implement a class Student with the following:

Instance variables: student ID, name, and marks of three subjects.

Methods to calculate the total marks, percentage, and display student details.

Create an object of the class and demonstrate the functionality.

code:
____

import java.util.Scanner;

class Student {
    // Instance variables
    int studentId;
    String name;
    int mark1, mark2, mark3;
    int total;
    double percentage;

    // Method to input student details
    void inputDetails() {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.print("Enter Student ID: ");
        studentId = sc.nextInt();
        sc.nextLine(); // Consume newline

        System.out.print("Enter Student Name: ");
        name = sc.nextLine();

        System.out.print("Enter marks for Subject 1: ");
        mark1 = sc.nextInt();
        System.out.print("Enter marks for Subject 2: ");
        mark2 = sc.nextInt();
        System.out.print("Enter marks for Subject 3: ");
        mark3 = sc.nextInt();
    }

    // Method to calculate total and percentage
    void calculateResults() {
        total = mark1 + mark2 + mark3;
        percentage = total / 3.0;
    }

    // Method to display student details
    void displayDetails() {
        System.out.println("\n--- Student Details ---");
        System.out.println("Student ID: " + studentId);
        System.out.println("Name: " + name);
        System.out.println("Marks: " + mark1 + ", " + mark2 + ", " + mark3);
        System.out.println("Total Marks: " + total);
        System.out.println("Percentage: " + percentage + "%");
    }

    // Main method to demonstrate
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Student s = new Student();
        s.inputDetails();
        s.calculateResults();
        s.displayDetails();
    }
}


output:
_______

Enter Student ID: 101
Enter Student Name: Alice
Enter marks for Subject 1: 85
Enter marks for Subject 2: 90
Enter marks for Subject 3: 80

--- Student Details ---
Student ID: 101
Name: Alice
Marks: 85, 90, 80
Total Marks: 255
Percentage: 85.0%
